Solar flare ribbons often exhibit fine structures consisting of multiple kernels and discrete brightness along with their complex structure and temporal variation. The discrete nature of ribbons in hard X-rays were pointed out by Asai etÂ al. (2002, 2004) and Krucker et al. (2003). The randomly orientated motion of isolated brightness within PRs is clearly visible in groups of UV footpoints on TRACE images moving as the flare progresses (Fletcher etÂ al. 2004). When viewed in high-resolution high-cadence HÎ±\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
